7. THE SOVEREIGNTY DIMENSION

ST-T1024 is designed to run on RISC-V—an open, sovereign instruction set architecture. Unlike ARM (UK/Japanese-controlled) or x86 (US-controlled), RISC-V has no single corporate owner.

Why RISC-V matters:

Aspect RISC-V ARM/x86
Control Open standard, global governance Proprietary, corporate-controlled
Licensing Free, no royalty $$$ per core
Customization Extensible Limited, controlled by vendor
Sovereignty Any nation can implement Dependent on foreign IP

The silicon path for ST-T1024 is a sovereign path.

